      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "REBEL RHAPSODY (1) handy gelding working nicely through the grades. Big improver second-up when he stalked the speed for a comfortable win over 1350m at Wyong. Gets an even better set-up today and the rise in weight is offset from the inside gate. Hard to hold out. UP TO MISCHIEF (4) appreciated the roomier Newcastle track second-up with an eye-catching second from near last on the turn over 1250m. Tricky map again and has a key jockey change today. Each-way. TESSY TEE (6) deep into the prep and can sit on the speed and take a hand in the finish today. Stepped up to the 1300m with a fighting third here at latest. Must respect from the draw. MURPHILLY (5) hasn't raced since finishing fourth over 1600m at Gosford four months ago. Prepared for this with a recent trial at Gosford. In the mix.",
